body:
Running Larabug with the Database cache driver can cause a `SQLSTATE[22001] | 1406 Data too long for column 'key'` issue if the generated exception string is over 255 characters. 

A (slightly sanitized) error message is below to see the generated exception string that caused me problems - but the cause is easy enough to understand as the relevant code is this which generates both the cache key and value and has no limit on length: 

   ```php
 private function createExceptionString(array $data)
    {
        return 'larabug.' . Str::slug($data['host'] . '_' . $data['method'] . '_' . $data['exception'] . '_' . $data['line'] . '_' . $data['file'] . '_' . $data['class']);
    }
```

Looking at the code I think I could just hash the string for the cache key to get a unique < 255 string for the key to avoid this issue, but not sure if that has implications I don't see. It could be done conditionally only when the cache driver is database to avoid hashing on redis etc?

Would that be an acceptable PR?

